      • setNetwork

        public Network.Builder setNetwork(java.lang.String network)

        Network.getNetwork() is a unique identifier for this network which can be referenced later for updates or queries.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If unset, an ID will be generated.
        Parameters:
        network - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.Network. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.Network.

      • setServices

        public Network.Builder setServices(Services services)

        Network.getServices() specifies which network services are configured on this network. These network services are expected to be accessible via the associated distributed virtual port group or distributed virtual switch.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If unset, network services may be automatically configured. If you want to disable any configuration of network services, explicitly set this class to empty.
        Parameters:
        services - New value for the property.

      • setIpManagement

        public Network.Builder setIpManagement(IPManagement ipManagement)

        Network.getIpManagement() describes how IP addressing is configured on this network.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If unset, this network becomes a DHCP network. Your DHCP server must support client identifiers to successfully enable a Supervisor.
        Parameters:
        ipManagement - New value for the property.

      • setFloatingIPAddress

        public Network.Builder setFloatingIPAddress(java.lang.String floatingIPAddress)

        Network.getFloatingIPAddress() is an IP address that provides a stable endpoint to the control plane. This address if specified must be an unused statically allocated IP address on the management network.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null and the management network is a static network, this address should be allocated in a static IP configuration which occurs when IPManagement.getDhcpEnabled() is set to false. If null and the management network is a DHCP network, The Supervisor will attempt to use the DHCP server to allocate this address. You should ensure the DHCP server is configured to persist IP addresses indefinitely using client identifiers if this configuration is used.
        Parameters:
        floatingIPAddress - New value for the property.

      • setProxy

        public Network.Builder setProxy(ProxyConfiguration proxy)

        Proxy configuration will be applied to the Supervisor. The proxy should be reachable from the management network and will be used for image pulling and container traffic exiting out of the Supervisor.

        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null the settings will be inherited from the vCenter settings if available.
        Parameters:
        proxy - New value for the property.
